#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1705
msgid "Proximity (raster distance)"
msgstr "Proximidad (distancia ráster)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1706
msgid ""
"Generates a raster proximity map indicating the distance from the center of "
"each pixel to the center of the nearest pixel identified as a target pixel. "
"Target pixels are those in the source raster for which the raster pixel "
"value is in the set of target pixel values."
msgstr ""
"Genera un mapa de proximidad ráster que indica la distancia desde el centro "
"de cada píxel al centro del píxel más cercano identificado como píxel de "
"destino. Los píxeles de destino son aquellos en el ráster de origen para los"
" que el valor de píxel de ráster está en el conjunto de valores de píxeles "
"de destino."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1712
msgid ""
"This algorithm is derived from the `GDAL proximity utility "
"<https://gdal.org/en/latest/programs/gdal_proximity.html>`_."
msgstr ""
"Este algoritmo se deriva de la `utilidad de proximidad GDAL "
"<https://gdal.org/en/latest/programs/gdal_proximity.html>`_."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1745
msgid "``VALUES``"
msgstr "``VALUES``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1751
msgid "**Distance units**"
msgstr "**Unidades de distancia**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1752
msgid "``UNITS``"
msgstr "``UNITS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1756
msgid ""
"Indicate whether distances generated should be in pixel or georeferenced "
"coordinates. One of:"
msgstr ""
"Indique si las distancias generadas deben ser en píxeles o coordenadas "
"georreferenciadas. Uno de:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1759
msgid "0 --- Georeferenced coordinates"
msgstr "0 --- Coordenadas Georreferenciadas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1760
msgid "1 --- Pixel coordinates"
msgstr "1 --- Coordenadas de pixel"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1765
msgid "``MAX_DISTANCE``"
msgstr "``MAX_DISTANCE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1775
msgid "``REPLACE``"
msgstr "``REPLACE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1781
msgid "**NoData value to use for the destination proximity raster**"
msgstr "**Valor de NoData a utilizar para la trama de proximidad de destino."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1791
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1861
msgid "**Proximity map**"
msgstr "**Mapa de proximidad**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1869
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:proximity``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:proximity``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1879
msgid "Roughness"
msgstr "Rugosidad"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1880
msgid ""
"Outputs a single-band raster with values computed from the elevation. "
"Roughness is the degree of irregularity of the surface. It's calculated by "
"the largest inter-cell difference of a central pixel and its surrounding "
"cell. The determination of the roughness plays a role in the analysis of "
"terrain elevation data, it's useful for calculations of the river "
"morphology, in climatology and physical geography in general."
msgstr ""
"Genera un ráster de banda única con valores calculados a partir de la "
"elevación. La rugosidad es el grado de irregularidad de la superficie. Se "
"calcula mediante la mayor diferencia entre celdas de un píxel central y su "
"celda circundante. La determinación de la rugosidad juega un papel en el "
"análisis de los datos de elevación del terreno, es útil para los cálculos de"
" la morfología del río, en climatología y geografía física en general."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1924
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1975
msgid "**Roughness**"
msgstr "**Rugosidad**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1978
msgid ""
"Single-band output roughness raster. The value -9999 is used as NoData "
"value."
msgstr ""
"Raster de rugosidad de salida de una sola banda. El valor -9999 se utiliza "
"como valor NoData."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1984
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:roughness``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:roughness``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1994
msgid "Sieve"
msgstr "Tamiz"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1995
msgid ""
"Removes raster polygons smaller than a provided threshold size (in pixels) "
"and replaces them with the pixel value of the largest neighbour polygon. It "
"is useful if you have a large amount of small areas on your raster map."
msgstr ""
"Elimina los polígonos ráster más pequeños que un tamaño de umbral "
"proporcionado (en píxeles) y los reemplaza con el valor de píxel del "
"polígono vecino más grande. Es útil si tiene una gran cantidad de áreas "
"pequeñas en su mapa ráster."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1999
msgid ""
"This algorithm is derived from the `GDAL sieve utility "
"<https://gdal.org/en/latest/programs/gdal_sieve.html>`_."
msgstr ""
"Este algoritmo se deriva de la `utilidad GDAL sieve "
"<https://gdal.org/en/latest/programs/gdal_sieve.html>`_."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2023
msgid "**Threshold**"
msgstr "**Umbral**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2024
msgid "``THRESHOLD``"
msgstr "``THRESHOLD``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2028
msgid "Only raster polygons smaller than this size will be removed"
msgstr "Sólo los polígonos ráster menores que este tamaño serán eliminados"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2030
msgid "**Use 8-connectedness**"
msgstr "**Usar conectividad 8**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2031
msgid "``EIGHT_CONNECTEDNESS``"
msgstr "``EIGHT_CONNECTEDNESS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2035
msgid ""
"If False, consider as neighbours only the (4) pixels that connect the edges "
"horizontally or vertically. If True, every pixel that touches an edge or a "
"corner is considered as neighbour."
msgstr ""
"Si es Falso, se consideran vecinos solo los (4) píxeles que conectan los "
"bordes horizontal o verticalmente. Si es True, se considera vecino cada "
"píxel que toca un borde o una esquina."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2037
msgid "**Do not use the default validity mask for the input band**"
msgstr ""
"**No usar la máscara de validez predeterminada para la banda de entrada**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2038
msgid "``NO_MASK``"
msgstr "``NO_MASK``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2048
msgid "Validity mask to use instead of the default"
msgstr "Máscara de validez a utilizar en lugar de la predeterminada"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2049
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2093
msgid "**Sieved**"
msgstr "**Tamizado**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2096
msgid "Output raster layer."
msgstr "Capa ráster saliente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2101
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:sieve``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:sieve``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2111
msgid "Slope"
msgstr "Pendiente"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2112
msgid ""
"Generates a slope map from any GDAL-supported elevation raster. Slope is the"
" angle of inclination to the horizontal. You have the option of specifying "
"the type of slope value you want: degrees or percent slope."
msgstr ""
"Genera un mapa de pendientes a partir de cualquier ráster de elevación "
"compatible con GDAL. La pendiente es el ángulo de inclinación con respecto a"
" la horizontal. Tiene la opción de especificar el tipo de valor de pendiente"
" que desea: grados o porcentaje de pendiente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2147
msgid "**Ratio of vertical units to horizontal**"
msgstr "**Ratio de unidades verticales a horizontales**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2154
msgid "``AS_PERCENT``"
msgstr "``AS_PERCENT``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2158
msgid "Express slope as percent instead of degrees"
msgstr "Expresa la pendiente como porcentaje en lugar de grados"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2171
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2230
msgid "**Slope**"
msgstr "**Pendiente**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2238
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:slope``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:slope``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2248
msgid "Terrain Ruggedness Index (TRI)"
msgstr "Indice de Rugosidad del Terreno (TRI)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2249
msgid ""
"Outputs a single-band raster with values computed from the elevation. TRI "
"stands for Terrain Ruggedness Index, which is defined as the mean difference"
" between a central pixel and its surrounding cells."
msgstr ""
"Genera un ráster de banda única con valores calculados a partir de la "
"elevación. TRI son las siglas de Terrain Ruggedness Index, que se define "
"como la diferencia media entre un píxel central y las celdas circundantes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2291
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2342
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2403
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2454
msgid "**Terrain Ruggedness Index**"
msgstr "**Índice de rugosidad del Terreno**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2345
msgid "Output ruggedness raster. The value -9999 is used as NoData value."
msgstr ""
"Salida de la trama de robustez. El valor -9999 se utiliza como valor NoData."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2351
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:triterrainruggednessindex``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:triterrainruggednessindex``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2361
msgid "Topographic Position Index (TPI)"
msgstr "Índice de Posición Topográfica (TPI)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2362
msgid ""
"Outputs a single-band raster with values computed from the elevation. TPI "
"stands for Topographic Position Index, which is defined as the difference "
"between a central pixel and the mean of its surrounding cells."
msgstr ""
"Genera un ráster de banda única con valores calculados a partir de la "
"elevación. TPI significa Índice de posición topográfica, que se define como "
"la diferencia entre un píxel central y la media de las celdas circundantes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2396
msgid "The number of the band to use for elevation values"
msgstr "El número de la banda a usar para valores de elevación"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2457
msgid "Output raster."
msgstr "Raster saliente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2462
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``gdal:tpitopographicpositionindex``"
msgstr "**Algoritmo ID**: ``gdal:tpitopographicpositionindex``"
